*Step 1: Install gedit*
$ sudo apt install gedit   (for ubuntu/debian)
$ sudo dnf install gedit      (for Fedora)
$ sudo pacman -S gedit       (for Arch Linux)
$ sudo zypper install gedit   (for OpenSUSE)


*Step 2: Setup Script*
$ gedit ezfind  (after gedit comes the NAme of the application, in this case it wil be ezfind.

now open the file "ezfind (script)" and copy & paste contents into gedit ad press "save".

now run the script with the following command. 

$ python3 ezfind


